<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial policy — Pholio"
  description="Pholio's editorial standards: sourcing, sponsorship, AI use, corrections, and conflicts of interest. Transparent rules for a travel publication."
  lang="en"
  schemaType="WebSite"
>
  <section class="max-page ptitle">
    <nav class="crumb"><a href="/">PHOLIO</a><span class="sep">→</span><a href="/about/">ABOUT</a><span class="sep">→</span><span class="cur">EDITORIAL POLICY</span></nav>
    <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-top:24px">Last updated 12 Apr 2026</div>
    <h1 class="hero-h1" style="margin-top:16px">Editorial policy.</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="max-page" style="padding-bottom:96px">
    <div class="max-prose prose-ed">
      <p class="drop-cap">Pholio is a travel publication. Everything we publish is written by people, fact-checked against local sources, and held to standards we describe openly below. If you find something that violates these rules, write to us and we'll correct or retract it.</p>

      <h2>1. Sources</h2>
      <p>Every answer is grounded in at least one of: (a) the author's lived experience, (b) on-the-ground reporting in the past six months, (c) interviews with local residents or businesses. We do not publish answers built from secondary web sources alone.</p>

      <h2>2. Sponsorship and affiliate links</h2>
      <p>Editorial pages carry no paid placement. We accept no money, comped meals, free accommodation, or press trips from restaurants, hotels, tour operators, or tourism boards.</p>
      <p>The Pholio app contains no advertising. We fund the publication through paid app subscriptions only.</p>

      <h2>3. AI and generated content</h2>
      <p>We do not publish AI-generated answers. We use AI internally for translation drafts, transcription, and fact-check lookups; every word you read is written and edited by a named person.</p>

      <h2>4. Corrections</h2>
      <p>When we get something wrong, we fix it visibly. Every correction is timestamped at the bottom of the article. Substantive changes (facts, recommendations, prices moving more than 20%) trigger a "Updated" badge on the article.</p>

      <h2>5. Seasonal review</h2>
      <p>Every article is reviewed at least twice a year by an editor other than the original author. Stale articles — defined as unreviewed for 12 months — are marked as such and deprioritised in search.</p>

      <h2>6. Complaints and removal</h2>
      <p>Businesses named in our articles can request a correction or right-of-reply by writing to <a href="mailto:editors@pholio.co">editors@pholio.co</a>. We don't remove critical mentions on request, but we will correct factual errors within five business days.</p>

      <h2>7. Conflicts of interest</h2>
      <p>Contributors disclose any personal or family connection to a business they write about. Such disclosures appear at the top of the relevant article.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
